Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} (if you'd like) for the
@spaghetti{180%grams}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1%unit}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Cut into thin strips,
sliced as thinly as you can.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams}, pepper and onion to the
pan. Season with salt and pepper if you'd like.

Fry, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked
through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

When the water is boiling, add the spaghetti to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

In the meantime, once the chicken is cooked, reduce the heat of the frying pan to
medium-high.

Add the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} and garlic to the chicken and
veg. Fry until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams},
@mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @water{125%ml} for the sauce and a good pinch of
@sugar{pinch} (if you'd like).

> See pantry for water amount. Add sugar if desired.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the sauce is thickened, taste and season with salt and pepper if you'd like. Add
the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and a knob of @?butter{1%knob} to the
sauce.

Add the cooked spaghetti to the sauce and toss to coat. Add a splash of water if you
feel it needs it.

> Kids Step: Mix the cheese and cooked spaghetti into the sauce using a spoon to bring
> it all together!

Share the spaghetti and sauce out between your serving bowls. Use a #fork{} or
#tongs{} to twist it into flowing swirls.

> Kids Step: Get swirling the spaghetti with a fork or tongs to make your whirlpools -
> a fork will make small ones and tongs will make big ones!

Enjoy!